Blocks.childText: 156 THE CHURCH: HOUR OF PRAYER. 8, 8, 8, 4, or 8, 8, 8, 6. (New.) J. P. POWELL. 1. My God! is an y hour so sweet From blush of morn to evening star, As that which calls me to thy feet-The hour of prayer. 2 431 The hour of prayer. (581) 3 When mystery clouds my darkened path, 2 Blest is the tranquil hour of morn, I'll check my dread, my doubts reprove; And blest that hour of solemn eve, In this my soul sweet comfort hath, That God is love! When, on the wings of prayer up-borne, The world I leave. 4 Oh may this truth my heart employ, 3 Then is my strength by thee renewed; And every gloomy thought remove; Then are my sins by thee forgiven; It fills my soul with boundless joy, Then dost thou cheer my solitude That God is love! With hopes of heaven. 433 Thy will be done. (900) 4 No words can tell what sweet relief There for my every want I find; 1 My God, my Father, while I stray What strength for warfare, balm for grief, Far from my home, on life's rough way, What peace of mind! Oh, teach me from my heart to say, "Thy will be done!" 5 Hushed is each doubt, gone every fear; My spirit seems in heaven to stay; 2 What though in lonely grief I sigh And e'en the penitential tear For friends beloved no longer nigh; Is wiped away. Submissive still would I reply, " Thy will be done!' 432 God is love. (86) 1 I can not always trace the way 3 If thou shouldst call me to resign Where thou, almighty One, dost move; What most I prize-it ne'er was mine, But I can always, always say, I only yield thee what was thine: That God is love. "Thy will be done!" 2 When fear her chilling mantle flings 4 If but my fainting heart be blest O'er earth, my soul to heaven above, With thy sweet Spirit for its guest, As to her native home, upsprings; My God, to thee I leave the rest: For God is love. 'Thy will be done!" Oriel, Key Ab. Delaware, Key Ab. The prayer J. P. POWELL 'Thy will be done'
